snippet.textDisplay:
Beautiful job on this one. I enjoyed the added polish on the production and it also added a few more shades to Pie's character. I liked that during the compulsory Pie-rant, he's declaring at the top of his lungs that saving the planet one clam at a time is a waste of time and then in the next scene he's walking the shoreline picking up litter... one piece of plastic at a time.

I would never want Tom to abandon the one man/one camera (/one ear piece ;)) "at the scene" reporting motif that has given this character so much momentum, but it would be awesome if he could do more features like this.

snippet.textDisplay:
Try it, you might like it? Mr J. Pie.
Like many foraged foods, seaweed emerged from the wilderness to capture the imagination of Britain's celebrity chefs. It has long been prized in Japan, where it is as commonplace as egg and chips. The Japanese have got it right: seaweed is a delicious, versatile and extraordinarily healthy food. It will also fill you up; a breakfast that includes seaweed will keep all but the most habitual snacker off the biscuits until lunchtime.

snippet.textDisplay: Why do people confuse plastic pollution with CO2?  Co2 is a life-giving, life-sustaining gas, which is at very low levels threatening life on this planet.  We are at 410 ppm, Plants and trees are most lush and grow fastest at around 2000 ppm. From the satellites pictures show that the planet has greened up since the slight increase in CO2, this can only be for the good of everyone.  We need more CO2 in the atmosphere , not less.  The earth used to be more than 15 X higher. We are Carbon, our food is carbon, we cannot live without co2, One of the reasons that the CO2 has become so low, is because sea crustacea, such as these mussels,  and trees, have sequested that Co2 from the air and from the biggest CO2 sink of all ... the SEA.  If we had MORE CO2, there would be more plant growth, so MORE FOOD to feed the starving masses.  Ever wondered why "they" have put this  climate hoax out ?  Could it be that they want less food to depopulate the planet via starvation?    Stop the African Continent from development,  stop them using their resources and by keeping them without electricity?  To give more people asthma? Wake up, CO2 is not a pollutant, Co2 is not a pollutant.  Now plastic pollution is the real issue... why is this not in mainstream news as the climate change hoax is?  It is a far far bigger  worrying issue.  Governments could stop the production of plastic cold turkey, they could order a clean up of our oceans... but no, too many globalists make money out of plastic.  So they confuse and mislead and eventually tax the people further for breathing.  Man made climate change is a complete and utter hoax to make money out of the masses and depopulate the planet.
